{
  "texts": [
    "Assuming we have constructed U k solving (37) modulo 𝔫 k+1, we now seek for U k+1 of the form U k + V with V ∈ 𝔫 k+1.",
    "We have DU k+1 + F (U k+1) = DU k + F (U k) + DV + (F (U k+1) -F (U k)).Since V ∈ 𝔫 k+1, and all terms in F (U k + V) -F (U k) involve at least one bracket with V, it follows that this last term is in fact in 𝔫 k+2, and so it can be ignored.",
    "By the invertibility of the induced map D on 𝔫 k+1 /𝔫 k+2, and the fact that DU k + F (U k) ∈ 𝔫 k+1, we can solve for V ∈ 𝔫 k+1 so that DU k + F (U k) + DV ∈ 𝔫 k+2, and this completes the proof.",
    "□Corollary A.5.",
    "Let (N, h) be a nilsoliton with soliton derivation D. Then, the soliton vector field may be chosen to be X D, the unique vector field whose flow is a one-parameter subgroup of automorphisms (η t) ⊂ Aut(N) satisfying (η t) * = exp(tD) for all t ∈ R.Lemma A.6."
  ]
}